[x] Read path falls back to a per-load ephemeral id when workspace_id is absent $replace the v5-from-path branch in effective_id() (load.rs:60) with a freshly-minted, non-persisted id per load: distinct per workspace so multi-workspace queries don't collide, never path-derived, never written back. queries work unstamped because the query graph and the ws:Workspace node insert both resolve through effective_id(). coordinates with retiring the v5 spec fallback (sibling action).$ !1 %2026-07-17T17:00 #019f6ea6-aa3b-7fb3-bfe3-02e132bd46a7
[x] Doctor flags a missing workspace_id and nudges init; no silent write-side stamping $identity is opt-in: init is the sole minting site — extend it to cover the home/user workspace, which nothing stamps today. doctor reports an unset workspace_id as an informational nudge to run init, never minting on a domain mutation. safe because the read-side ephemeral fallback makes queries work unstamped, so persistence is polish, not correctness.$ !1 %2026-07-17T17:00 #019f6ea6-737b-7f83-91bb-bd8143ca9e9e
